          <p>Ondiege is the founder, choreographer and director of Dance Into Space company. He is an accomplished actor and choreographer whose dance work borrows heavily from African dance vocabularies and addresses existential issues while working with movement and elements of theatre in the conventional and unconventional community spaces.  He has been using contemporary dance to empower communities of non-dancers, disabled artists and non-disabled performers.</p>
          <p class="mt-6">He trained in performing arts at the Nairobi Theatre Academy in Kenya in the early 90’s before going to Bagamoyo College of Arts in Tanzania in the mid 90’s, International School of dance in Senegal, Tzek School of modern dance in Moscow and was a guest artist at the Bremer Tanztheatre in Germany between 2000 and 2003. In 2005 he started the mixed ability dance projects in Kenya as a choreographer and has since trained and worked with more than 150 disabled dancers and performers across the country.</p>
